    "mechanism": "Model selective attention as independent sampling from a probability distribution over space or time. For each feature dimension (color, identity), compute the correlation of errors when sampling attention samples under varying spatial or temporal uncertainty. When spatial or temporal resolution is poor, each feature is independently selected by random sampling from the distribution, leading to occasional feature-binding errors (illusory conjunctions). Veridical perception occurs when the sampled coordinates are sufficiently precise that multiple independently sampled features originate from the same spatial or temporal region.",
