    "doi": "10.1177/0146167210383440",
    "mechanism": "Decompose observed affect misattribution into a multinomial latent-variable model with three component processes: affective response to the true stimulus cause, affective response to the apparent cause, and confusion probability between apparent and real source. The model partitions the joint distribution of judgments to estimate the contribution of each process. Inference recovers the parameters via likelihood maximization over the observed response distribution. This provides a framework for separating implicit attitudes (as measured by the affect misattribution procedure) from conscious confusions or affective priming.",
